19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 18-11-110(d), concerning the prohibition on
22 land ownership by a prohibited foreign-party-controlled business, is amended
23 to read as follows to clarify a criminal offense:
24 (d) A prohibited foreign-party-controlled business entity shall that
25 violates this section upon conviction be is guilty of a an unclassified
26 felony punishable by not more than two (2) years' imprisonment in the custody
27 of the Division of Correction or a fine of fifteen thousand dollars
28 ($15,000), or both.
29
30 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code ยง 18-11-802(8)(B) and (C), concerning the
31 definition of "significant interest" and "substantial control" as used with
32 respect to the foreign ownership of agricultural land, are reenacted to
33 ratify the decision by the Arkansas Code Revision Commission to change
34 references to "subdivision (5)(A)" to "subdivision (5)" in order to correct
35 reference errors.
36 (B) An interest of thirty-three percent (33%) or more held
