10 SECTION 3. DO NOT CODIFY. CONSTRUCTION AND LEGISLATIVE INTENT.
11 It is the intent of the General Assembly that:
12 (1) The enactment and adoption of this act shall not expressly
13 or impliedly repeal an act passed during the regular session of the Ninety-
14 Fifth General Assembly;
15 (2) To the extent that a conflict exists between an act of the
16 regular session of the Ninety-Fifth General Assembly and this act:
17 (A) The act of the regular session of the Ninety-Fifth
18 General Assembly shall be treated as a subsequent act passed by the General
19 Assembly for the purposes of:
20 (i) Giving the act of the regular session of the
21 Ninety-Fifth General Assembly its full force and effect; and
22 (ii) Amending or repealing the appropriate parts of
23 the Arkansas Code of 1987; and
24 (B) Section 1-2-107 shall not apply; and
25 (3) This act shall make only technical, not substantive, changes
26 to the Arkansas Code of 1987.
